
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Musicmatic

class Song {
  +title: String
  +year: Integer
  +length: Integer
  +genre: String
}

class Artist {
  +name: String
  +dateOfBirth: Date
  +websiteURL: String
}

class User {
  +id: Integer
  +name: String
  +address: String
}

class RegularUser <|-- User
class BusinessUser <|-- User

class Album {
  +title: String
  +trackNumber: Integer
}

class Single {
  +title: String
}

class Hit {
  +title: String
  +trackNumber: Integer
}

class PurchaseSuggestion {
  +albumTitle: String
  +userSimilarity: Float
}

' Relationships
Song "1" -- "1" Artist : belongs to
Artist "1" -- "0..*" Song : has

User "1" -- "0..*" Song : owns (BusinessUser only)
User "1" -- "0..*" Album : owns (RegularUser only)

Album "1" -- "1..*" Hit : contains
Hit "1" -- "1" Album : part of

Single "1" -- "1" Song : represents
Hit "1" -- "1" Song : represents

RegularUser "1" -- "0..*" Album : owns
RegularUser "1" -- "0..*" Single : can buy
RegularUser "1" -- "0..*" PurchaseSuggestion : receives

BusinessUser "1" -- "0..*" Single : uploads
BusinessUser "1" -- "0..*" Hit : uploads

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Song**: Contains title, year, length, genre.
- **Artist**: Has name, date of birth, and website URL. Artists are uniquely identified by name.
- **User**: Base class with ID, name, and address. Can be either `RegularUser` or `BusinessUser`.
- **RegularUser**: Can buy singles or albums and receive purchase suggestions.
- **BusinessUser**: Can upload songs (as singles or hits).
- **Single**: Represents a standalone song that can be bought.
- **Hit**: A song that can be part of an album.
- **Album**: Contains multiple hits, ordered by track number.
- **PurchaseSuggestion**: A suggestion for a regular user based on similar purchasing behavior.

